auteed Mushroom Medley, Lemon Herb Roasted Vegetables, Baked Tomato Risotto with Basil, Spinach and Ricotta Pie.\n\nI need to structure 10 files with specific formatting patterns. Four files should have titles split across multiple lines, four should include category or serving information before the title, and two should contain OCR errors. Each file needs to be 15-60 lines, with spillover files running longer. I'm planning which recipes to assign to each pattern type, making sure to avoid any from the exclusion list when selecting examples like Polish gingerbread with nuts, grilled squid, and pumpkin pie with spiced cream for the split-title category. I need to double-check my selections against the exclusion list to ensure I'm not duplicating existing recipes. Looking at the files already generated, I see \"Piernik z Orzechami.generated.21.txt\" which means that recipe is already taken. Let me verify each choice against the provided exclusion list more carefully—the user specifically asked for different recipes than the ones already generated, and I should cross-reference my list with what's already been created. I need to systematically check against the exclusion list rather than guessing. Looking at what's already generated, I should pick recipes that definitely aren't there. Piernik z Orzechami works since it's not in the list. Grilled Squid with Garlic is safe too. But I need to skip Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli since that's already generated, and Schabowy since it's in the exclusions. For the remaining slots, Thai Basil Chicken fits, along with Risotto with Porcini since the exact title isn't duplicated. Bigos Wiosenny could work as a variation from the existing Bigos recipes. - English main\n8. **Kopytka z Grzybami** - Polish pasta dish\n9. **Risotto with Porcini** - English main\n10. **Piernik Miodowy** - Polish gingerbread (checking... \"Piernik Miodowy.generated.21.txt\" is in exclusion. Skip.)\n\nI need to start fresh and select 10 distinct recipes that