{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Z8VNpXTa68c4hnJre3kAD","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Scallop and Saffron Risotto.generated.22.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79979-f917-445a-83c4-99cb8a3cfd6e","uuid":"0989643c-48df-4863-8668-58ca54f3af5c","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Scallop and Saffron Risotto.generated.22.txt","content":"SCALLOP AND\nSAFFRON\nRISOTTO\n\nA luxurious risotto showcasing the delicate sweetness of bay scallops paired\nwith the golden, aromatic notes of saffron. This dish is perfect for\nentertaining special guests and impresses with its elegance.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 1 lb large scallops\n- 6 cups chicken or seafood stock, warmed\n- 1 small pinch saffron threads\n- 1/4 cup white wine\n- 1 shallot, minced\n- 1 1/2 cups arborio rice\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh lemon zest\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Steep saffron threads in 1/4 cup warm stock for 10 minutes.\n2. Heat olive oil in a large, heavy-bottomed pot over medium heat.\n3. Sauté shallot until translucent, about 2 minutes.\n4. Add rice, stirring constantly for 1-2 minutes until slightly translucent at edges.\n5. Deglaze pot with white wine, stirring until absorbed.\n6. Add warm stock one ladle at a time, stirring frequently.\n7. After 12 minutes, pat scallops dry and season with salt and pepper.\n8. In a separate skillet, sear scallops 2 minutes per side in remaining oil. Set aside.\n9. Continue adding stock until rice is creamy and tender, about 18-20 minutes total.\n10. Stir in saffron infusion, butter, and Parmesan.\n11. Top with seared scallops, lemon zest, and serve immediately.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
