{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_019AxqxNzdJjj8dyGzENBaZG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MToDkxpQUkUMF93tsBFeYL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Kompot Jabłkowy.generated.22.txt","content":"KOMPOT\nJABŁKOWY\n\nKompot is a traditional Polish fruit drink, served hot or cold as a refreshing\nbeverage. This apple version is simple, wholesome, and perfect for any season.\nThe aromatic spices create a warming drink suitable for family meals.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 8 medium apples, peeled, cored, and sliced\n- 6 cups water\n- 1/2 cup sugar\n- 3 whole cloves\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 1/4 tsp ground nutmeg\n- Juice of 1/2 lemon\n- 2 tbsp honey (optional)\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Slice apples into thin wedges, discarding seeds and core.\n2. Combine water and sugar in a large pot and bring to boil.\n3. Add apple slices, cloves, cinnamon stick, and nutmeg.\n4. Reduce heat and simmer 15-20 minutes until apples are tender but not mushy.\n5. Add lemon juice to taste.\n6. Strain if desired for a clearer compote, or leave fruit pieces in.\n7. Stir in honey if using for extra sweetness.\n8. Serve hot in winter months, chilled in summer.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTIONS:\nServe as a refreshing drink alongside meals or as a light dessert. Pairs well\nwith simple cookies or pastries. Store in refrigerator up to 5 days.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":76912,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":76912},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79979-f917-445a-83c4-99cb8a3cfd6e","uuid":"45200433-440b-440f-9005-19b98e2afdf0"}
