{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_019AxqxNzdJjj8dyGzENBaZG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0189ukXdMRERRuz96pqVLm9k","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Pan Seared Cod.generated.22.txt","content":"Jesień | Dania główne | Dla 4 osób\n\nPAN SEARED COD\n\nThis simple preparation allows the delicate, flaky texture of cod to shine.\nThe golden crust from pan-searing contrasts beautifully with the tender flesh\ninside. A perfect weeknight dinner that tastes restaurant-quality.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 4 cod fillets (6 oz each)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 3 tbsp olive oil\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- Juice of 1 lemon\n- Fresh thyme sprigs\n- Fleur de sel for finishing\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Pat cod fillets completely dry with paper towels. This is crucial for crust.\n2. Season generously on both sides with salt and pepper.\n3. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until just smoking.\n4. Carefully place cod skin-side down in the pan.\n5. Resist the urge to move the fish—let it cook undisturbed for 4-5 minutes.\n6. Using a thin spatula, gently flip the fillets.\n7. Add butter, garlic, and thyme sprigs to the pan.\n8. Cook another 3-4 minutes until fish is opaque throughout.\n9. Finish with fresh lemon juice and fleur de sel.\n10. Serve immediately while still warm.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTIONS:\nServe with roasted root vegetables or a crisp green salad with shallot vinaigrette.\nA dry Sauvignon Blanc pairs beautifully with this dish.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":76912,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":76912},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79979-f917-445a-83c4-99cb8a3cfd6e","uuid":"92ced5fb-36b3-4e11-afd8-61748fd90c0f"}
